> - Bad TCPv4 checksums messages 
> (on a ppp link, they happen mostly during heavy ftp transfers)
Those are debugging but arent enabled in production (eg 2.0 kernels). If you
are using IDE disks look at the hdparm command and the -u option.
> - RealPlayer v5 doesnt work properly
> a strange problem, if i let it sit there alone it works
> but as soon as i switch window, move the window or try
> to multitask (:) the player stops and prints the following
> to stdout :
> ****audio: write error: 502 bytes errno: 11
Its a bug in RealPlayer than 2.1.x shows up but 2.0.x didnt. There's a magic
command for fixing Real Player in /usr/src/linux/Changes nowdays.
> - Until 2.1.131 applying a patch was fast at first but it was getting
> slow to a crawl in the end. When i synced i could heard the system
> syncing -very- slowly.
> (i'm use IDE disks)
So 2.1.131 is behaving but kernels before that didnt ?
Alan
